Class: it is a template or blueprint to the java object/instance


Object: it is instance of a class, means based the class template we can create physical entity, 
        which hold memory space in RAM(Heap) memory.
        
new keyword: new operator/keyword which helps JVM to create an object based on given class name.
             and also it will allocate certain memory(RAM(Heap memory)) to java object.
             
Class Properties:
	- fields
	- initializers
		- constructors
		- blocks
	- methods
	- inner/nested classes
	
	
Task-1: Write a java program, let us take Employee class as template with id, name, role, department 
        and salary
        
        1. create an object of Employee class
        2. initialize an object of an Employee class
        3. print employee object details.
         